args: Uprising:\nA simple game with dire stakes.\nIts only rule? Abandon all pretense.
In indolence, justice!\nIn selflessness, defeat!\nTo the ＂chill＂ go the spoils!
Considered from another perspective,\nkindness and advantage share an inverse\nrelationship in this game of do-or-do-not.
(Mitsuhide? Unusual to see her out of bed.\nMaybe this could be my chance to...\nWait, what's she...?)
(Hmm... She's running the Uprising game,\nbut she looks awfully distraught... Surely\nit'd be okay for me to ask her what's up.)
My mouse friend. She usually rides\naround on my head.
Ah, right. And when did she disappear?

She was gone when I woke up this
afternoon. Oh, whatever should I do?
If she were to get lost in the woods and
become some fiend's dinner, I...!
You'd lose the game if you helped her\nlook for the mouse.
And Mitsuhide, your mouse is sleeping\ncomfortably in your room, isn't she?
Mice—I mean, rats! I was so close.
As crocodile as they come.\nI almost had you, too.
My victory's only a matter of time, y'know.\n*yawn* Guess it's back to the drawing—\nnapping?—board for me. Gooood luck!
Thank you, Jurota. You're a lifesaver.
Think nothing of it. But you must remain\nvigilant, Your Highness. Mitsuhide is a\ncunning opponent.

She even went to the trouble of winning
over the people of the Halidom in
preparation. Do not be fooled by
her recumbent facade.
(Come to think of it, roping half the folks\nin the castle into her schemes would be a\nlot of trouble, so why would Mitsuhide...?)

(There had to have been an easier way to
steal the kingdom if she REALLY wanted to
do it. Why would she go this far with her
Uprising game?)
Final Day of the Uprising Game
You hangin' in there all right,\n{player_name}?
Remember, if you don't get me to\ndo something for someone else today...
I'll lose the game. I know.\nBut it's not over until it's over.
Honestly, I didn't think you'd tough it out\nfor this long. You're made of sturdy stuff.
(That being said, kinda feels like we're\ncoming right down to the wire here.)
(They saw right through my ＂boo-hoo, I\ncan't find Bonnie＂ strategy...)
(Buuuut, I wonder what he would do if I\ncollapsed right here, hacking and cou—)
{player_name}, this is bad!\nA horde of fiends has attacked the\nvillage beyond the forest!
{player_name}, the Imperial\nArmy is advancing on a town to the\nnorth! They number over two hundred!
This isn't good. If the prince has to divide\nhis forces, I'm not sure either group would\nbe sufficient to contend with these threats.
Elisanne, Jurota: You two take the\nothers and head to the town up north.\nI'll shapeshift and handle the fiends!
You can't fight alone! There are too many\nof them, and—
Ah-ah-ah. The Uprising game isn't over yet.
You didn't forget the rules, did you?\nIf you act to help someone, you lose.
What are you babbling about at a time like\nthis?! People could be in actual danger!
It's a question of what's important to you.
Your own circumstances, or other people's.\nWhich one is it, {player_name}?
...Elly, Jurota, you take the others and go.\nI'll handle the fiends.
At least let me accompany you! Even with\nyour power of shapeshifting, going alone\nis tantamount to suicide!
It'll be fine. Believe in me.\nNow hurry up and go!
So you've made your choice, huh?
I guess we can call the game a wrap.\nScore 1 for Mitsuhide, 0 for—
Wrong. I'm not doing this for others.\nI'm doing it for me.
If I don't go right now, I, the leader of\nNew Alberia, will be the one to regret it!
Everyone, please...listen to me.\nI want you to help me do this!
I realize how ridiculous it is for me to ask\nyou to indulge me when you've already\ndeclared your allegiance to Mitsuhide.
But please! Help me to protect the people!
...Sorry, Mitsuhide. Turns out there ain't\nnobody more fit to be our leader what\nfor him after all.
Honestly, I wish you'd lean on us like this\nall the time.
If you're goin' out there, there's no way\nwe can just sit around twiddlin' our\nbowstrings.
Huh, I didn't see this coming.\nTouché, Prince. Touché.
Are you quite sure it's all right for you\nto sit this one out?
Oh, YOU'RE here? Welp, looks like I'm\ngonna have to go along too, aren't I?
I would imagine your uprising is far past\nthe point of ending in a happily-ever-after.
Yeah, yeah, I know. Circumstances being\nwhat they are, I'll let you handle this,\nDaikokuten.
Meh. He scored one on me, so the least\nI can do is throw the guy a bone.
